g^AA^T - B^Tg^B & = g^A_{lora}A^T - B^Tg^B_{lora}, \\
\Rightarrow \quad
B^TBX + XAA^T & = -\frac{1}{s^2}(B^TB)^{-1}g^A_{lora}A^T,
\end{aligned}
\end{equation}
which is a Sylvester equation. This equation has a unique solution for $X$ if and only if $B^TB$ and $-AA^T$ have no shared eigenvalues.
\end{proof}

