Assume $\Omega$ is convex and the velocity model $\bm{v}_{\bm{\theta}}(\bm{x},t)$ is $M$-Lipschitz in $\bm{x}$ (uniformly on $t$). 
Let $p_{\bm{\theta},t}(\bm{x})$ be the probability path of the reflected CNF induced by $\bm{v}_{\bm{\theta}}(\bm{x},t)$ starting from the same prior distribution $p_0(\bm{x})$.
